39 - Styling a lists's markers

Notes
    * Markers are the bullets in an unordered list or the numbers in an ordered list.
    * ul {
        list-style-type: disc;
        list-style-type: circle;
        list-style-type: square;
        OR 
        list-style-image: url ("images/heart.png");
    }
    * The default list-style-type for ordered lists is decimal-1, 2, 3 etc.
    * You can change it to decimal-leading-zero-01, 02, 03 etc.
    * lower-alpha-a, b, c etc.
    * upper-alpha-A, B, C etc.
    * lower-roman-i., ii., iii. etc.
    * upper-roman-I., II., III. etc.
    * ol.second-level {
        list-style-type: upper-roman;
    }

